Sure, I can help you with that. Here are some examples of how I can solve integration questions:

1. Indefinite Integrals:
   - ∫x² dx = x³/3 + C
   - ∫sin(x) dx = -cos(x) + C
   - ∫e^x dx = e^x + C

2. Definite Integrals:
   - ∫[0, 1] x³ dx = [x^4/4]_[0, 1] = 1/4
   - ∫[π/2, π] cos(x) dx = [sin(x)]_[π/2, π] = 0
   - ∫[0, 2] e^(-x²) dx = [erf(x)]_[0, 2] ≈ 0.9953

For more information and examples on integration, you can refer to the following links:

* [Integration Rules and Formulas](https://www.khanacademy.org/math/calculus-1/integration-intro/integration-rules/a/integration-rules-and-formulas)
* [Definite Integrals](https://www.mathsisfun.com/calculus/definite-integrals.html)
* [Integration by Substitution](https://www.symbolab.com/solver/step-by-step/%5Cindefinite%20integral%20of%20(x%5E2%20-%201)%2F(x%5E2%20-%202%20x%20%2B%201)

If you have a specific integration question that you need help with, please feel free to ask me. I'll be happy to provide a step-by-step solution for you.
